27. What do the following two code fragments do?
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++)
       for (int j = 0; j < N; j++)
           if (i != j) System.out.println(i + ", " + j);

    i j N output
    0 0 3
    0 1   0, 1
      2   0, 2
      3
    1 0   1, 0
      1
      2   1, 2
      3
    2 0   2, 0
      1   2, 1
      2
      3

    A: This program prints pairs with sum N, N+1, N+2 ...

    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++)
       for (int j = 0; (i != j) && (j < N); j++)
           System.out.println(i + ", " + j);

    i  j  N  output
    0  0  4
       1     0, 1
       2     0, 2
       3     0, 3
       4
    1  0     1, 1
       1
       2     1, 2
       3     1, 3
       4
    2  0     2, 0
       1     2, 1
       2
       3     2, 3
       4
    3  0     3, 0
       1     3, 1
       2     3, 2
       3
       4

    1, 1, 1
    1, 1, 1
    1, 2, 8
    1, 3, 9
    A: Programs prints powers of i up to N - 1

